cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a technique to improve the generalization ability of deep RL agents, which is a common problem in machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on using randomized neural networks to achieve this goal. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper uses images as input, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper applies the proposed technique to robotics control tasks, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.RO (Robotics).
